modules.description: Parses and generates XML-based property list data using a strict implementation of the Apple PropertyList DTD. It handles nested lists, dictionaries, strings, and binary data through custom type definitions. Used to serialize configuration files and exchange structured data between OCaml applications and macOS systems.

Provides functions to parse and print property list data from channels, strings, or byte sources, and to encode and decode signal streams for XML representation. Works with tree structures representing plist values, byte streams, and signal/token sequences. Used to convert XML-formatted plists to in-memory trees, serialize trees to strings, and process streaming XML data without building full trees.
